I"ñ<ol>
  <li>Install <code class="highlighter-rouge">irssi</code> &amp; <code class="highlighter-rouge">bitlbee</code>:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>apt-get update <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> apt-get <span class="nb">install</span> <span class="nt">-y</span> bitlbee irssi
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Edit <code class="highlighter-rouge">/etc/bitlbee/bitlbee.conf</code>:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>DaemonInterface = 127.0.0.1
DaemonPort = 6667
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Enable &amp; start <code class="highlighter-rouge">bitlbee</code> service:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>systemctl <span class="nb">enable </span>bitlbee
systemctl start bitlbee
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Run <code class="highlighter-rouge">irssi</code></li>
  <li>Add <em>Bitlbee</em> server &amp; connect:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>/server add -auto -network bitlbee 127.0.0.1 6667
/connect bitlbee
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Register <em>Bitlbee</em> user:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>register &lt;$BITLBEE_PASSWORD&gt;
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Add Twitter account:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>account add twitter &lt;$TWITTER_HANDLE&gt;
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Authorize Twitter account:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>account on
</code></pre></div>    </div>
    <blockquote>
      <p>This will open a new chat window with a Twitter OAUTH2 link in it. Open the link in a browser and authorize <em>Bitlbee</em> on Twitter, then copy the displayed auth code back to the chat window.</p>
    </blockquote>
  </li>
  <li>Disable tweeting from <em>Irssi</em> (optional):
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>account twitter set commands strict
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Update</strong>: <a href="https://blog.twitter.com/developer/en_us/topics/tools/2017/announcing-more-functionality-to-improve-customer-engagements-on-twitter.html">Since Twitter crippled their API for 3rd-party-apps</a>, itâ€™s not possible anymore to use the Stream API. To avoid errors, the stream feature needs to be turned off for Bitlbee:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>account twitter set stream off
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>To connect &amp; identify to the <em>Bitlbee</em> server automatically on every start of <em>Irssi</em>, run:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>/network add -autosendcmd "/msg &amp;bitlbee identify &lt;$BITLBEE_PASSWORD&gt;; wait -bitlbee 2000; /window goto &amp;bitlbee; /window close" bitlbee
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Save <em>Irssi</em> configuration:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>/save
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>

